[thinking] **Clarifying configuration issues**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about how the conditional config includes methods related to fixtures when using caller javassist.tools. The user-code filter is key here since it tells the agent which classes to filter out. If the user-code filter excludes everything and includes javassist, that suggests javassist is seen as user code too.
[thinking] 
[thinking] There’s a potential issue with the helper name "verifyUnsupportedDynamicClassLoading" catching an error during load class reads if an assertion error arises. That might happen if the parent load class isn't the same. If there’s a parent fallback, matching sizes could be fine, but there’s concern with the `Loader` constructor always delegating "javassist.Loader".
[thinking] 
